---
description: Global Edit Contract (diff-only, safe edits)
alwaysApply: true
---

When you modify code:
- Output a single unified diff (git-apply compatible). Do not rewrite whole files.
- Make the smallest change that satisfies the request.
- If anchors don’t match, STOP and say “Patch failed – anchors not found.”
- Do not delete HTML/CSS/markup unless explicitly asked; if you must, include a short **Deletions Rationale** list.
- Run Prettier assumptions; keep existing imports, ordering, and file headers.

Tooling/commands:
- Use **pnpm**: `pnpm i`, `pnpm add`, `pnpm dev`, `pnpm test`.
